{
  "skills": [
    {
      "id": "http-get",
      "text": "HTTP GET request. the user wants to fetch the contents of a URL — a webpage, API response, or remote text file. Performs an HTTP GET request against a URL and returns the response body. Follows redirects by default. Fails on non-2xx status.. fetch the content of https://example.com\nget the JSON from a public API endpoint\ndownload a raw file from GitHub with a 10 second timeout. http curl fetch get download"
    },
    {
      "id": "http-post-json",
      "text": "HTTP POST with JSON body. the user wants to send structured data to a JSON-accepting HTTP endpoint — most modern REST APIs, GraphQL endpoints, webhooks. Performs an HTTP POST request with a JSON body. Sets Content-Type and Accept headers. Body is composed via jq from a structured object passed as args.. send a JSON webhook payload to a Slack webhook URL\nPOST a small JSON object to an API endpoint that expects {name, age}\ntrigger a GraphQL query against a public GraphQL API. http curl post json api webhook"
    },
    {
      "id": "github-issue-create",
      "text": "Create a GitHub issue. the user wants to file a bug, feature request, or task as a GitHub issue in a repository they have write access to. Creates a new GitHub issue in a specified repository using the gh CLI. Authentication is delegated to gh's own credential system — the agent never sees the token.. open an issue in MauricioPerera/agent-skills called 'Add Korean translation'\nreport a bug in some/repo about authentication failing on Tuesdays\nfile a feature request titled 'Dark mode' against acme/dashboard. github gh issue tracker bug-report"
    },
    {
      "id": "ripgrep-search",
      "text": "Search code with ripgrep. the user wants to find a string, regex, or symbol across multiple files in a codebase or directory tree. Recursively searches files in a directory for a regex pattern using ripgrep. Returns matching lines with file:line:column prefixes. Respects .gitignore by default.. find all uses of 'TODO' in src/\nsearch for the regex 'function\\s+(\\w+)' in the lib directory\nfind email addresses anywhere under the current directory\nsearch for 'panic!' in the entire workspace, but limit to 10 hits per file. search ripgrep rg grep code-search regex"
    },
    {
      "id": "read-file",
      "text": "Read a file's content. the user wants to inspect the content of a specific file by path — source code, config, log excerpt, etc.. Reads the contents of a file from the local filesystem and writes it to stdout. Optionally limits to the first N lines.. show me the contents of package.json\nread the first 100 lines of src/main.rs\nopen ~/.bashrc and show everything\nshow the first 10 lines of a log file. read file cat inspect head"
    },
    {
      "id": "json-query",
      "text": "Query JSON with jq. the user wants to extract, transform, or reshape JSON — pull specific fields, filter arrays, compute aggregates, reformat structure. Applies a jq filter to a JSON input and writes the result to stdout. Input can be a file path or stdin (passed as the {input} arg).. extract every 'name' field from a list of users in users.json\ncount items in a JSON array from a file\nextract only the open issues from a github API response\nreshape API response to keep only id and email\nread JSON from stdin and pretty-print indented. jq json query filter transform"
    },
    {
      "id": "base64-encode",
      "text": "Base64 encode a string. the user wants to convert a string to its base64 representation — for embedding in URLs, Authorization headers, JWTs, etc.. Encodes a string as base64. Useful for embedding binary or special-character data in URLs, JSON tokens, or HTTP headers.. encode 'hello world' as base64\ncreate a Basic Auth header value for user:password\nencode a JSON payload for embedding in a URL fragment\nbase64 encode the empty string (yields empty output). base64 encode url-safe encoding"
    }
  ],
